In the New York City Campaign for Mayor, we have two candidates. 

One is Curtis Sliwa, founder of the guardian angels, and trying his darnedest to make red berets look good.

The other is former NYPD Captain Eric Adams.

Adams is coasting. He's assuming that he's Democrat in NYC, therefore he wins. So he's mostly in hiding. 

Did no one tell him that Democrats have lost FIVE of the last SEVEN elections?

He's not running any ads on any channels I've seen. I haven't seen a single ad on Facebook. The most I've seen out of Adams is "Curtis is running against me, he's racist?" Also, he spouts "Law & Order! Law & Order!" like he's an ad for Dick Wolfe... but never says how.

The cops I talk to tell me Eric Adams was never a cop, just a politician in a uniform. Back in the day, he supported Louis Farrakhan against Mayor Dinkins.

All I hear from the radio stations is how Adams "retired" from the NYPD before he could be prosecuted in half a dozen different scandals.

It doesn't surprise anyone when #Google and #YouTube decides to censor "climate deniers" on their platform recently. 

They've censored talk about "Covid-19", "elections being rigged in 2020", and have punished those who use "decisive" or "disparaging" language or terminology like illegal aliens or uttering the name of Eric Ciaramella.
It shouldn't surprise anyone that #bigtech go to extreme lengths to defend the establishment powers to hold tight control of the commons, or the exercising of free speech on very popular tech platforms.
All par for the course I suppose.
(If you're still seeing this post it means that there is still free speech on alt-tech)
#freespeech #censorship #climatechange #politics
